This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new method for distance metric learning using support vector machines. The paper also includes experiments on image recognition tasks (handwritten digit recognition, face verification, and person re-identification), which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of large-scale datasets and the focus on efficiency in training could also suggest the sub-categories of software development (cs.SD) and computational linguistics (cs.CL), respectively.
